title: SWPL as it happened - Aberdeen, Motherwell, Partick Thistle & Rangers win
title_page: SWPL as it happened - Aberdeen, Motherwell, Partick Thistle & Rangers win: BBC Sport - BBC Sport
maintext:
Goodbye
That's all from me this afternoon but there's still plenty of SWPL action to come!
Hibs v Glasgow City is up next (16:10 BST) followed by the rearranged Celtic v Hearts match at 19:45 and you can watch both of those live on the BBC Sport Scotland website, app and iPlayer - don't say we're not good to you!
We'll also have all the reaction from today's games over on our dedicated Scottish Women's Football page over the coming days.
Post
Glasgow City have the chance to reduce that gap to Rangers again as they travel to Hibs.
Hibs, on the other hand, can go level on points with Rangers - and within two of the league leaders - with a win.
FULL-TIME Partick Thistle 4-1 Dundee United
While Brian Graham will be disappointed his side weren't able to keep a clean sheet, he'll surely be delighted with the four goals.
It's more disappointment for Dundee United though as they remain bottom of the table.
